  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Cerebral microemboli (ME) are frequently generated during major orthopaedic surgery. The
      primary objective of this study was applying novel transcranial Doppler (TCD) ultrasound
      software algorithm to quantify (ME load/15 minutes) and qualify (particulate vs. gaseous) ME,
      detected as high-intensity transient signals (HITS) in both middle cerebral arteries (MCAs)
      before and after orthopaedic surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
